  <div class="lesson-bridge"><span class="lb-icon">📚</span><div><strong>Lesson Foundation:</strong> This is the direct application of <strong>§07 Unresolved Dilemmas</strong> (Issue 1 — cryptocurrency). The same Badges of Trade test from Issue 2 (property) applies to crypto — but with even less judicial guidance. The corporate purpose (Meridian Crypto Treasury was set up to trade digital assets) creates an almost irrebuttable inference of trading intention.</div></div>
  <table class="tbl">
    <tr><th>Transaction</th><th>Amount</th><th>Likely Tax Treatment</th><th>Certainty</th></tr>
    <tr><td>ETH sold (14-month hold)</td><td class="nc">S$1,600,000 gain</td><td class="neg">Taxable — entity set up to trade; intention = trading</td><td><span class="tag tag-r">High</span></td></tr>
