<!-- ══════════════ VN COMPARE ══════════════ -->
<div class="sec lesson-section" id="vn-compare">
  <span class="sec-num">§ 08 · LESSON+CASE</span>
  <h2>Vietnam ↔ Singapore Tax System — Full Comparative Bridge</h2>
  <div class="sec-rule"></div>
  <table class="tbl">
    <tr><th>Feature</th><th>🇻🇳 Vietnam</th><th>🇸🇬 Singapore</th><th>Meridian Implication</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Tax Territory</td><td>Worldwide for residents; territorial for non-residents</td><td>Strictly territorial — only SG-source or remitted foreign income</td><td>Meridian Vietnam's income is outside SG scope unless remitted/sourced in SG (Issues 4, 10)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Corporate Rate</td><td>20% standard; 10% preferential</td><td>17% flat; Pioneer 0–10%</td><td>VN charges 20% on Meridian Vietnam; SG charges 10–17% on SG entities</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Capital Gains</td><td>20% on securities; 25% on property transfer</td><td>No CGT — trading test applies</td><td>Meridian's property gain (Issue 2) is tax-free in SG if capital; taxable in VN at 25% in equivalent structure</td></tr>
    <tr><td>VAT / GST</td><td>10% standard; 5% reduced; multiple rates</td><td>9% single rate; zero-rated; exempt</td><td>VN has richer rate differentiation; SG's partial exemption (Issue 5) has no VN equivalent — VN uses direct allocation</td></tr>
    <tr><td>WHT — Management Fees</td><td>FCT: 5% VAT + 10% CIT on gross (Foreign Contractor Tax)</td><td>s45: 17% CIT WHT on gross</td><td>Issue 4: Meridian Vietnam's management fee is subject to SG s45 WHT (17%) when received from SG payer — and VN FCT applies in reverse when SG provides services to VN</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Anti-Avoidance</td><td>Art. 8 Law on Tax Admin — substance test</td><td>ITA s33 — dominant purpose counterfactual</td><td>Issue 14 (dividend strip): VN GAAR uses substance-over-form; SG GAAR uses counterfactual — different analytical frameworks reaching similar results</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Transfer Pricing</td><td>Decree 132/2020/ND-CP — arm's length</td><td>ITA s34D — OECD-aligned arm's length</td><td>Issue 10: both jurisdictions apply arm's length; but VN does not grant corresponding adjustment automatically — MAP required</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Legal Hierarchy</td><td>Constitution → Luật (Law) → Nghị định (Decree) → Thông tư (Circular) → Quyết định (Decision)</td><td>Constitution → Acts → Subsidiary Legislation → IRAS Guidance → Case Law</td><td>VN's Thông tư (Circular) is functionally equivalent to IRAS e-Tax Guide but has stronger quasi-legal status. VN Decree ≈ SG subsidiary legislation in hierarchy.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Property Tax</td><td>Non-agricultural land use tax (low, area-based)</td><td>Annual Value based — 4–36% residential</td><td>Issue 8: SG property tax is economically significant and calculated on notional AV, not actual income — no VN equivalent mechanism</td></tr>
  </table>
</div>

<!-- ══════════════ DILEMMAS ══════════════ -->
<div class="sec both-section" id="dilemmas">
  <span class="sec-num">§ 07 · LESSON + CASE</span>
  <h2>Singapore's Seven Unresolved Tax Dilemmas — Applied to Meridian</h2>
  <div class="sec-rule"></div>
  <div class="box box-unresolved"><div class="box-title">1. BEPS Pillar Two vs Existing Pioneer Certificates (Issue 1)</div><p>Can Singapore constitutionally impose QDMTT on entities holding valid Pioneer certificates? No case law. No advance ruling framework. Singapore's most financially significant unresolved corporate tax question in 2025. <strong>Meridian exposure: S$900,000/year.</strong></p></div>
  <div class="box box-unresolved"><div class="box-title">2. Dividend Stripping — GAAR Without Specific Provision (Issue 14)</div><p>Does ITA s33 apply to deny the one-tier dividend exemption where shares are acquired specifically to extract accumulated retained earnings tax-free? No Singapore case law on dividend stripping. <strong>Meridian exposure: S$1,360,000 binary risk.</strong></p></div>
  <div class="box box-unresolved"><div class="box-title">3. Crypto-to-Crypto Swaps — Are They Taxable Disposal Events? (Issue 12)</div><p>Is an ETH→USDC swap a "disposal" triggering gain recognition? IRAS 2020 crypto guide is silent. Every major comparable jurisdiction (UK, Australia, US) treats it as a disposal. Singapore has not stated its position. <strong>Meridian exposure: S$45,000 swap gain unresolved.</strong></p></div>
  <div class="box box-unresolved"><div class="box-title">4. DeFi Yield Farming — Recognition, Valuation & GST Character (Issue 12)</div><p>When is DeFi income recognised? At what value? Is it a financial service (GST exempt) or a goods supply? No IRAS guidance on DeFi as of 2025. <strong>Meridian exposure: S$120,000 income characterisation risk.</strong></p></div>
  <div class="box box-unresolved"><div class="box-title">5. Platform Workers CPF — ITA Deductibility Gap (Issue 13)</div><p>PWA 2024 mandates CPF contributions for platform workers; ITA s14(1)(c) allows deduction only for employees. Platform workers are not employees under ITA. <strong>Meridian exposure: up to S$2.6M/year non-deductible from 2029.</strong></p></div>
  <div class="box box-unresolved"><div class="box-title">6. Double GST on OVR + Reverse Charge (Issue 6)</div><p>Where an overseas vendor is OVR-registered AND a Singapore recipient applies reverse charge — who corrects the double-charge and how? No IRAS correction mechanism published. <strong>Meridian exposure: systematic overpayment of GST on overseas digital services.</strong></p></div>
  <div class="box box-unresolved"><div class="box-title">7. s33 GAAR Override of DTA Benefits — Vienna Convention Tension (Issue 11)</div><p>Can Singapore invoke domestic GAAR to deny treaty benefits that are validly available under a bilateral DTA? The Vienna Convention on Law of Treaties requires good faith treaty performance. The MLI PPT provides a treaty-level denial mechanism — but s33's application to DTA benefits remains controversial and untested at appellate level.</p></div>
</div>

