  {q:"Meridian PropCo (a Singapore company) purchases a residential property for S$3,800,000. The market value is S$3,850,000. What is the correct ABSD basis under SDA s22C?",opts:["S$3,800,000 (purchase price)","S$3,825,000 (average of price and MV)","S$3,850,000 (MAX of price and MV)","S$3,800,000 (price takes precedence)"],ans:2,d:'medium',pts:10,neg:5,src:'Issue 7 + Lesson §06',exp:"SDA s22C: ABSD is charged on the HIGHER of purchase price or market value. MAX(S$3,800,000, S$3,850,000) = S$3,850,000. At 65% ABSD (corporate entity), this produces S$2,502,500 in ABSD alone. Using purchase price instead of MV would understate the ABSD by S$32,500."},
